dspace-development.title: Troubleshoot and document the solution for authentication issues on the Symplectic Elements QA and Production environments

comments.body:
Connecting over the PowerShell requires the following:
```powershell
$sqlConn = New-Object System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection
$sqlConn.ConnectionString = "Data Source=CISDR300W;Initial Catalog=elements;Integrated Security=False;User ID=Sympsql_Dev;Password=[SECRET]"
$sqlConn.Open()
```

~This may be unrelated, but `rt4ds` does not appear to be accessible for the OAR `dev` server~:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/91943597-d76cc480-ecca-11ea-8eaa-a847f08a5ad0.png)

This is functioning, but requests issued by Elements (e. g. https://oar-dev.princeton.edu/rt4ds/repository/publication/135284) do not resolve - https://oar-dev.princeton.edu/rt4ds/repository does respond however, so this may just be a configuration error.

There are only two configuration files on the OIT server infrastructure for the `rt4ds` service which are not symbolic links to DSpace installation files. These do not seem to have any significantly different settings: https://gist.github.com/jrgriffiniii/d7f61d19d938ae82b3301f39b0ac6494
The `rt4ds` configuration is set to use the Oracle database driver for the oar-dev.princeton.edu environment.

The logs for `rt4ds` were being generated until 08/18/20:

```
dspace@gcp-oar-dev1:/dspace/log$ ls -lt | grep rt4ds
-rw-rw-r--  1 dspace dspace   1050629 Aug 18 13:33 rt4ds.log.99
-rw-rw-r--  1 dspace dspace   1052263 Aug 18 13:33 rt4ds.log.98
```

`/home/dspace/apache-tomcat/conf/logging.properties` on `gcp-oar-dev1` and `/etc/tomcat/logging.properties` on `cisdr204l.princeton.edu` are essentially identical between server environments (with the exception of UTF-8 support for `gcp-oar-dev1`)
`/dspace/rt4ds/config/log4j.properties` is properly in place on `gcp-oar-dev1`, but the logs are not being generated - is this expected behavior?

Once tomcat was started, the following was logged:

```
INFO: Deploying deployment descriptor [/home/dspace/apache-tomcat-7.0.104/conf/Catalina/localhost/rt4ds.xml]
Sep 02, 2020 1:56:42 PM org.apache.catalina.loader.WebappClassLoaderBase validateJarFile
INFO: validateJarFile(/mnt/disks/oardevdatastore/prod-copy/dspace/webapps.static/rt4ds/WEB-INF/lib/servlet-api-2.5.jar) - jar not loaded. See Servlet Spec 3.0, section 10.7.2. Offending class: javax/servlet/Servlet.class
Sep 02, 2020 1:56:43 PM org.apache.catalina.startup.TaglibUriRule body
INFO: TLD skipped. URI: http://java.sun.com/jstl/fmt is already defined
Sep 02, 2020 1:56:44 PM org.apache.catalina.startup.TaglibUriRule body
INFO: TLD skipped. URI: http://java.sun.com/jstl/fmt is already defined
Sep 02, 2020 1:56:44 PM org.apache.catalina.startup.TldConfig execute
INFO: At least one JAR was scanned for TLDs yet contained no TLDs. Enable debug logging for this logger for a complete list of JARs that were scanned but no TLDs were found in them. Skipping unneeded JARs during scanning can improve startup time and JSP compilation time.
Sep 02, 2020 1:56:51 PM org.apache.catalina.startup.HostConfig deployDescriptor
INFO: Deployment of deployment descriptor [/home/dspace/apache-tomcat-7.0.104/conf/Catalina/localhost/rt4ds.xml] has finished in [9,040] ms
```

Within `/dspace/webapps.static/rt4ds/META-INF/maven/org.dspace.modules/rt4ds/pom.xml`, version `2.4` was specified for the JAR:

```
<dependency>
                   <groupId>javax.servlet</groupId>
                   <artifactId>servlet-api</artifactId>
                   <version>2.4</version>
                   <scope>provided</scope>
                </dependency>
```

I updated this to 2.5. but the error persisted.
A number of `/dspace/dspace-rt4ds.cfg` and `/dspace/dspace.cfg` settings were outdated or incorrect for communicating with the Elements server.

`oar-dev.princeton.edu` will need to be able to access `oaworkflow-dev.princeton.edu`, and this seems to be prevented by firewall rules. This has been requested with https://princeton.service-now.com/service?id=ticket&is_new_order=true&table=incident&sys_id=9764a5c91b8f1410b69cca292a4bcb1b
https://princeton.service-now.com/service?id=ticket&table=change_request&sys_id=068669c51bcf1410b69cca292a4bcbff&view=sp was created for the production environment.

PulfaExporter should create download links for file types not supported by UV

comments.body:
Couple of things:

1. This came up in another working group I'm in. Do we need persistent links to these downloads? Like should there be an ARK that goes to the download link? Maybe not important for this.

2. Maybe not important, but the example ZIP is pretty nuts - it's like 8 levels of folders deep which seems to replicate the hydra_sources directory structure. Maybe something to fix on that example record?

3. An empty broken viewer is going to show up in PULFA as soon as this record is marked complete, and I'm not sure adding a download link will fix it. We'll have to test it.

Anyways, as a first step it seems like to close this ticket I'll just make it put the download link in for ZIPs, but some thoughts about future potential issues above.

@tpendragon Those sound like good things to look at before we complete the items.  Some thoughts:

1. I haven't heard any desire for ARKs linking to the downloads as opposed to the finding aid or other landing page.

2. I agree the deep folder structure of that object isn't great, and reflects a lot of the Figgy server setup and the bagging structure of the content. @cwulfman should probably checkin with Annalise and make sure the Zip files in Figgy have the structure we want to preserve, and not anything extra.

3. It would be great to prevent an empty viewer showing up. Either making the viewer iframe show the download link, or suppressing the display of the viewer completely if it's not going to work, would be much better.
